A vintage 1990s-style illustration of an overflowing wooden card catalog drawer bursting open, with dozens of manila folders and index cards cascading outward in a dynamic spiral pattern. Each folder appears weathered with dog-eared corners and coffee stains, suggesting frequent use. The scene is set in a warm, amber-toned library environment with dust particles floating in shafts of golden afternoon light streaming through unseen windows. In the background, more towering card catalog cabinets fade into soft focus, their brass handles gleaming. The color palette emphasizes sepia tones, cream, and burnished gold, evoking the nostalgic feeling of pre-digital information organization and the treasure hunt of finding essential documentation.
